FBIS4-3547 "drchi078_c_94005" FBIS-CHI-94-078 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 Central Eurasia Li Peng, Niyazov Attend Agreement Signing Ceremony Li Peng, Niyazov Attend Agreement Signing Ceremony OW2204083994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0825 GMT 22 Apr 94 OW2204083994 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Ashkhabad [Ashgabat], April 22 (XINHUA) -- China and Turkmenistan signed another three documents on bilateral cooperation today, the third or last day of Chinese Premier Li Peng's official visit to this Central Asian country. Premier Li Peng and President S. A. Niyazov attended the signing ceremony, which took place at the presidential palace. The documents signed today include an agreement on China providing loans to Turkmenistan, a protocol on regular consultations between the foreign ministries of the two countries and an exchange of notes on China presenting a batch of materials to Turkmenistan. Meanwhile, the delegation of Chinese entrepreneurs traveling with the premier has so far signed six letters of intent and two agreements with Turkmen businessmen. Under one of the agreements, the China National Construction Engineering Corporation and Turkmenistan's Ministry of Construction will set up a brick-making joint venture here to produce 30 million bricks annually. The other was signed between the China Council for the Promotion of International Trade and Turkmenistan's Chamber of Industry and Commerce for establishing cooperative ties.
